HEADWORD: Pitots tube
<hw>Pi*tot's" tube`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Hydraul.)</fld> <def>A bent
tube used to determine the velocity of running water, by placing the
curved end under water, and observing the height to which the fluid
rises in the tube; a kind of current meter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitpan</ent>⟦br⟧
